    "created_at": "2019-05-22T01:47:52Z",
    "updated_at": "2019-05-22T01:48:27Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "thanks, got it to work. In case anybody else needs to do something similar:\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n// set inputs in memory\r\nuint256[4] memory input;\r\n// input[0] = ...\r\n// input[1] = ...\r\n// input[2] = ...\r\n\r\n// create a memory region for return value\r\nuint256[1] memory retval;\r\n\r\n// success == 1 if the call is successful \r\nuint256 success;\r\nassembly\r\n{\r\n    success := staticcall(not(0), 0x85, input, 0x80, retval, 32)\r\n}\r\n\r\nif (success != 1) {\r\n    return address(0);\r\n}\r\n```",
